race.comment: THINK TANK (4) continues to savage the line and is edging closer to a breakthrough, last start finishing just a long neck away over 1800m at Morphettville. Will drift back again from the draw and be charging hard late. WARRANDYTE ROAD (11) dominated over this course and distance last start when sent forward in a sharp return to form. No reason he can't go on with it now. THE TANK (9) doesn't win out of turn but his peaks measure up. Gets a nice pull in the weights over WARRANDYTE ROAD with the claimer engaged after chasing gamely into fourth here two weeks ago. Can give this a big shake. ALCHIAN (2) found the line strongly last start to grab third over 1800m at Morphettville. Has a good record at the trip and is among the chances. ANNANDA (8) comes through the same race and is another that races well here. Worth considering.
